  Redo the whole thing not to depend on gtk+-2.0 by default, and enable
  --with-gnome theoretically for gnome-1.4.

*xscreensaver-4.06-r1 (26 Oct 2002)

  26 Oct 2002; Martin Schlemmer <azarah@gentoo.org> xscreensaver-4.06-r1.ebuild:
  Change "xml" flag to "xml2".  Remove "gnome" USE flag.  Change "gtk" in USE
  to depend on gtk+2, and also add libglade2.  If gtk+ is not in USE, make it
  depend on gdk-pixbuf.  This should close bug #9619.

*xscreensaver-4.06 (24 Oct 2002)

